  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/6216d0631ddbd0def1371870993d4f40.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=312 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > Every action costs you time (a turn). You make the decision, do you hire more workers?</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.poster.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=302 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.webm?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.mp4?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Each worker will have traits that can either complement or clash with others.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Employees will also form friendships that can lead to something more. Or maybe they'll just hate each other's guts?</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Each interaction affects their stress levels. Higher the stress the less productive they are.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > How about firing the underperforming employee? </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/99c5289fb07f1fe2a6ccadce781254b3.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=416 /></span></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > People will react to firings too, sometimes it can be the catalyst to make a profit</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > But firing a beloved employee can have negative consequences</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > Or maybe tell your top performer to take a break before they have a breakdown? </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/7819d78fa43955f312053edcee1203ec.poster.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=630 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/7819d78fa43955f312053edcee1203ec.webm?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/7819d78fa43955f312053edcee1203ec.mp4?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > Or try to poach a new customer from one of your competitors </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/13d7a6c73db6c8edf07af21b62895d65.poster.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=302 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/13d7a6c73db6c8edf07af21b62895d65.webm?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/13d7a6c73db6c8edf07af21b62895d65.mp4?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > The key is in balancing your actions to get the best out of your employees, fail here and everything will fall apart </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/3ae111e244d9b162172c47fd7020df15.poster.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/3ae111e244d9b162172c47fd7020df15.webm?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/3ae111e244d9b162172c47fd7020df15.mp4?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/6216d0631ddbd0def1371870993d4f40.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=312 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > Every action costs you time (a turn). You make the decision, do you hire more workers?</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.poster.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=302 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.webm?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/67011692bd53d5dc98a254cc9cd0cadc.mp4?t=1731947181\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Each worker will have traits that can either complement or clash with others.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Employees will also form friendships that can lead to something more. Or maybe they'll just hate each other's guts?</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Each interaction affects their stress levels. Higher the stress the less productive they are.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > How about firing the underperforming employee? </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2837490/extras/99c5289fb07f1fe2a6ccadce781254b3.avif?t=1731947181\" width=600 height=416 /></span></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > People will react to firings too, sometimes it can be the catalyst to make a profit</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > But firing a beloved employee